From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [DEBUG] systemd: BOOTPROF markers (systemd-init/selinux-split/early-init-steps/udev)

Adds 0100-DEBUG-bootprof-unit-load-timing.patch to the systemd recipe (SRC_URI).
Adds instant init-step markers across the relabel-done -> generators window to
pinpoint the ~162ms early-init wait, plus split selinux (policy-load / relabel),
the systemd-init span, and udev event markers. Pure markers, no logic change.
Requires qcom_bootprof SELinux allow rule + initramfs tracefs mount. Drop to
restore stock.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [debug instrumentation]
---
diff --git a/meta/recipes-core/systemd/systemd/0100-DEBUG-bootprof-unit-load-timing.patch b/meta/recipes-core/systemd/systemd/0100-DEBUG-bootprof-unit-load-timing.patch
