+From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000100 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
+Date: Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
+Subject: [DEBUG] core+udev: BOOTPROF markers (systemd-init, selinux split, early-init steps, udev)
+
+Instrumentation only. src/shared/bootprof.{c,h} (libshared; PID1 + udevd)
+write Perfetto-compatible marker slices to the top-level trace_marker
+(retry-open, snprintf-safe, every-failure logging). Pure observation: no
+change to systemd/udev control flow.
+
+Slices/points (rootfs-only "systemd-init" span, main() start -> initial txn):
+  - selinux-policy-load        (main.c: mac_selinux_setup)
+  - selinux-relabel(/dev,/run) (mount-setup.c)
+  - init-step:{parse_configuration, apply_protect_system, collect_fds,
+    cg_has_legacy, dlopen_libmount, initialize_runtime, manager_new}
+    (instant markers to pinpoint the ~162ms wait between relabel and
+     generators; gap between consecutive markers = that step's cost)
+  - generators, unit-load {enumerate_perpetual, enumerate{enum:.<type>},
+    dispatch_load_queue}, coldplug
+  - udev: trigger / manager on_uevent / worker per-event begin+end
+
+log_info() BOOTPROF timing lines kept. Read markers: cat .../tracing/trace.
+Drop to restore stock.
+
+Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [debug instrumentation]
